React-PDF is a library for creating PDF files using React components, with support for both web and Node.js environments. Key features include:

- Creates PDFs, not displays them (different from another library with a similar name)
- Installable via `yarn add @react-pdf/renderer`
- Supports rendering PDFs in the browser using `PDFViewer`
- Allows saving PDFs to files in Node.js environments
- Uses a React-like styling approach with `StyleSheet.create()`

Example basic usage:
```javascript
import { Document, Page, Text, View, StyleSheet } from '@react-pdf/renderer';

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  page: { flexDirection: 'row', backgroundColor: '#E4E4E4' },
  section: { margin: 10, padding: 10, flexGrow: 1 }
});

const MyDocument = () => (
  <Document>
    <Page size="A4" style={styles.page}>
      <View style={styles.section}>
        <Text>Section #1</Text>
      </View>
    </Page>
  </Document>
);
```

The project is open-source, MIT licensed, and welcomes community contributions.

